Caught in a Web  
  
  *Here's the chromatic interlude part (played mostly unisono by bass,*  
  *guitar and keyboard). Petrucci plays this on a 7-string, the tab here is*  
  *for a 6-string guitar - it's transposed up an octave (except bars 2,4 and*  
  *15 to end).*  
  *This whole part makes a great warm-up excersise (when you play it*  
  *slower). It's also perfect for practicing cross-picking and*  
  *string-skipping - check out the sextuplets at the end...*  
  
